reviews.review_text:
althea nice show, nice sets 

i took the time to write a review about how this althea actually conveys something like what the actual sound experience of a show really was, how it sounds live, more or less, especially as it starts.  this was common in analog but rare for digital.  who's the sax?  
good stuff

Good Run Nice opening night to a very good New Year's run.  The 12/30/89 is the gem of the run in my book - it was a magical night for me so I'm biased!  
Answer to previous question - Clarence Clemmons sitting in on sax...good, but we'd all be spoiled by Branford in NY!
